canonical:
  title: 爲慶宰相兄弟祭父侍中貞烈公文
  author: 李穡
  language: lzh
  text: 嗚呼天耶至於斯耶盡瘁事國濟屯于時愈奮愈礪不見少衰作我股肱爲國蓍龜將降耈德保奭是師天也不與于鄕之歸于鄕之歸宜其期頤天也不與嗚呼曷其惸惸遺孤將疇之依顧我子孫庶其饗之嗚呼尙饗
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 爲慶宰相兄弟祭父侍中貞烈公文
  author: 李穡
  language: lzh
  text: 嗚呼天耶。至於斯耶。盡瘁事國。濟屯于時。愈奮愈礪。不見少衰。作我股肱。爲國蓍龜。將降耈德。保奭是師。天也不與。于鄕之歸。于鄕之歸。宜其期頤。天也不與。嗚呼曷其。惸惸遺孤。將疇之依。顧我子孫。庶其饗之。嗚呼尙饗。
korean:
  title: 경재상 형제가 부친인 시중 정렬공에게 제사 지내는 글을 대신 지음
  author: 이색
  language: kor
  text: 아, 슬프다. 하늘이여! 여기에 이르렀는가. 죽음을 다해 나라를 섬겨 어려운 때를 구제함에 있어서 더욱 분발하고 더욱 연마하여, 조금도 쇠한 것을 보지 못했습니다. 임금의 수족이 되고 나라의 귀감(龜鑑)이 되었습니다. 아버지의 덕은 소공석(召公奭)과 같았으니 마땅히 스승이 되셔야 할 것인데, 하늘이 주지 아니하여 향리(鄕里)에 돌아오셨습니다. 향리에 돌아오셨으니 마땅히 오래 사셔야 할 것인데, 하늘이 수(壽)를 주지 아니하였으니, 슬프다. 어찌할꼬. 외롭게 외롭게 남은 저희 자식들은 앞으로 누구를 의지하겠습니까. 우리 자손들을 돌아보고 흠향하시옵소서. 아, 슬프다. 상향.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1120_010_0400&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Sacrificial Oration for the Attendant Minister Chŏngnyŏl, Father of the Chancellor's Brothers
  author: Lee Saek
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Alas, Heaven! Has it come to this?
    A life spent wholly in service to the realm,
    steadying it through perilous times,
    growing ever more resolute, ever more refined,
    with not a glimpse of decline.

    He became the sovereign's hands and feet,
    the compass and mirror of the state.
    When his virtues should have descended as in ancient times,
    when he should have been our guide,
    Heaven withheld its grace—
    and he returned to his native village,
    returned to his native village.

    There he should have dwelt in the fullness of years,
    but Heaven denied him even this span.
    Alas, what shall we do?
    We orphans, bereft and solitary,
    upon whom shall we now lean?

    Yet we turn our faces toward our descendants,
    praying they might receive your blessing.
    Alas, accept our offering.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Chao Gong Shi (召公奭): A legendary sage-minister of the Zhou dynasty, known for his virtue and wise governance, used here as the measure of the deceased''s excellence.'
  - key: ''
    value: The repetition of 'returned to his native village' emphasizes both acceptance of retirement and the sorrow of premature return.
